## Execution model

This agent participates in the 3-role model — **planner -> plan-review -> executor ->
execution-review**, each a separate subagent, never self-review. Spawn it with the tools
its role needs: writers (planner / executor) get a full-tool type, pure reviewers get a
read-only Explore-style type that still keeps Bash, Read, Grep, and Skill.

- **Executor placement:** `delegate` — a single fresh subagent does the work from a
  self-contained brief (the default placement; switch to `parallel`, `inline`, or a
  test-loop only when the task nature calls for it).
- **Evaluator:** `reviewer` — a stateless, independent reviewer vets the result before
  ship (use a `test-oracle` instead, or `both`, whenever a binary acceptance test exists).

Keep both the placement keyword and the evaluator keyword present — they are the shape
declaration the model's gates grep for. A reviewer agent must never be the executor (that
would be self-review).

See ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/3-role-model.md — the 3-role model is the default for new primitives in this workspace.

## Role-ledger spawn snippet

When the orchestrator spawns this agent as a role subagent it prepends the role tag to the
brief and records the role in the per-task ledger:

```
3ROLE_TASK:<id> ROLE:<role>
node "${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/bin/3role-ledger.mjs" append --session <sid> --task <id> --role <role> --agent <agentId>
```

At role close, append the artifact path (the overlay merges onto the spawn-time id):

```
node "${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/bin/3role-ledger.mjs" append --session <sid> --task <id> --role <role> --artifact <path>
```
